132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 167
H.P. 100 House of Representatives, January 14, 2025
An Act to Provide 2 Hearing Aids to MaineCare Members with
Diagnosed Hearing Loss
Reference to the Committee on Health and Human Services suggested and ordered printed.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative GRAHAM of North Yarmouth.
Cosponsored by Representative: SHAGOURY of Hallowell.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 22 MRSA ยง3174-ZZ, sub-ยง2, as enacted by PL 2017, c. 237, ยง1, is
3 amended to read:
4 2. Required reimbursement. The department shall provide reimbursement for a
5 hearing aid for one each hearing-impaired ear of an individual enrolled in the MaineCare
6 program in accordance with the following requirements:
7 A. The hearing loss must be documented by a primary care provider or an audiologist
8 licensed pursuant to Title 32, chapter 137;
9 B. The hearing aid must be provided by an audiologist or a hearing aid dealer licensed
10 pursuant to Title 32, chapter 137; and
11 C. The hearing loss must meet the requirements established by the department in rule
12 regarding the individual's severity of hearing loss.
13 The department shall provide reimbursement for a hearing aid for the 2nd hearing-impaired
14 ear of an individual enrolled in the MaineCare program if the individual meets requirements
15 established by the department by rule regarding the individual's severity of hearing loss,
16 enrollment in school, enrollment in vocational training, employment needs or the needs
17 identified by a primary care provider.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This bill requires the MaineCare program to provide reimbursement for a hearing aid
2200 for each hearing-impaired ear of an individual enrolled in the MaineCare program. Under
2211 current law, the MaineCare program provides reimbursement for a hearing aid for one
2222 hearing-impaired ear of an individual enrolled in the MaineCare program, with additional
2233 requirements as established by rule for coverage of a hearing aid for the 2nd hearing-
2244 impaired ear.
